Truckloads of ISWAP fighters struck a military base at Gajibo, Borno, on Tuesday, killing five soldiers and carting away arms ammunition.
Eyewitnesses said the terrorists came in 15 gun trucks.
Days ago, the insurgent took over a town in Borno, and planted their flag there.
